The paper deals with wireless broadcasting and network coding, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The proposed protocol involves user cooperation and scheduling, which are also relevant to system and control theory (cs.SY). The use of batched network code suggests a potential application in multimedia communication (cs.MM). Finally, the analysis and simulation of the protocol's performance may involve distributed computing (cs.DC).
